name: name of simulation
Icount: (dict) total number of spikes for each unit
vbinedges: edges of voltage bins for V-histograms in time
unitrates: firing rates of all units individually
sat_t: time args for saturation per cycle
wspec_extent: boundaries of wspec in time and frequency space
ripple: Index of beginning and end of ripple event
Pthr: power threshold used to determine significance of instfreq
ifreq_discr_t: Time args of peak-to-peak measure for instantaneous network frequency
ifreq_discr: peak-to-peak measure for instantaneous network frequency
v_hist: histogram of voltages at the compiled 21 sample phases
frac_multispikers: approx. Fraction of units spiking several times per cycle
v_std_mean: mean standard deviation of membrane potentials from time-dep. mean
v_std_std: standard deviation of standard deviation of membrane potentials from time-dep. mean
v_av_mumin: estimate of mumin based on mean membrane potential (no gauss fit)
v_av_sigmin: estimate of sigma_min based on mean membrane potential (no gauss fit)
v_std: standard deviation of membrane potential in n average phases of a ripple cycle as determined in gauss analysis
popspk_av: average population spike over one cycle
v_av: average membrane potential over one cycle
I_dc: DC current in Malerba model (array of size Nint)
v_av_mumin_sd: standard deviation around estimated mumin over cycles, based on mean membrane potential (no gauss fit)
